                  <scriptDesc>
                     <scriptNote>Italian semi-cursive and Ashkenazi square script, partially
                           punctuated. Leon ben Yoshu῾ah de Rossi
                              of Cesena inscribed with his name in a colophon, Reggio di
                           Emilia, [5]226 (or [5]224?) [1466 or 1464] (folio 377v). The workshop of
                           one of the artists of Duke Borso d'Este, probably Giorgio d'Alemagna. Ashkenazi square and Italian semi-cursive script, partially
                           punctuated. Yitsḥaḳ ben Obadiah ben
                              Daṿid of Forli: inscribed in the colophon, Bologna, 23 Elul, [5]187 [1427], folio 418v. Italian semi-cursive, partially punctuated.</scriptNote>
                  </scriptDesc>
